My Husband asked me for a Saturday night date break out and to meet at Deniz (Fort Greene) Brooklyn. I strolled over and met him with the anticipation of trying out their (newly added to the menu) Deniz Burger. One bite. Good Lawd. IT IS ONE OF THE BEST BURGERS I HAVE EVER HAD IN MY LIFE ! No joke. The layering of the ingredients is the key for me. My Husband believes it is the cooking style of the burger that delivers the flamed broiled taste. Whatever it is, they nailed it! We begged our Server to tell the cook to NEVER change the layering or it take it off the menu. Try it. Then what do you think it is? Maybe it’s made with love which the world needs more of anyway. THANK YOU Deniz for this memorable night.  Andrea BF

The food is EXCELLENT!!!!! Flavorful, healthy, fresh, and presented well.  The meal is also presented quickly. The atmosphere is very casual and relax. I enjoyed dinning outdoors.  The staff is very friendly.  However,  the only reasons why I have rated them 4 stars oppose to 5 is because I was there on a date.  We were having an intimate and engaging conversation while eating our meal.  Which could easily be observed by how were engaged with one another. Body language, direct eye contact etc.  However, about every 3 minutes our conversation was interrupted by a staff member to ask if we were alright? Do we need anything? Or for small talk.. I know they were being friendly but dude...they were totally disturbing the vibe.  I tried to politely tell them they are doing an excellent job and if we needed anything we will call them. But they did't seem to get it. And continued to interrupt our conversation and laughter.  Another thing....they kept coming over filling our glass with water even when we said we were fine. And just took 1 sip from the glass. Besides the constant interruption the waitstaff reached across our plate of food to pour the water oppose to simply walking to the other side of the table which was closer to the glass to pour.  In conclusion. I would highly recommend this restaurant because of the cleanliness, excellent food, great location,  cool relaxing atmosphere, Decent price.  Friendly staff that means well.  The issues with the staff can be quickly resolved with proper training from management.  Great spot to dine at with friends, family, co-workers to have a casual conversation.But not recommended for a date. Tooo many annoying  interruptions. It will most likely kill the mood and memories you are trying to create.

I cannot think of any reason what the thinking behind the decision was to put in the service charge to our bill. Other than maybe financial discrimination perhaps. Because when I asked the waiter Ahmed why it was added he explained it is added to everyone's bill when it obviously is not.
